Part 1

part a)

Exp <- function(x, k) {
  exp_val <- 1
  for (i in 1:k) {
    exp_val <- exp_val + x^i/factorial(i)
  }
  exp_val
}

Exp(3, 2)
## [1] 8.5

part b)

sample_mean <- function(x) {
  n <- length(x)
  mean_val <- 0
  for (i in 1:n) {
    mean_val <- mean_val + x[i]
  }
  
  mean_val/n
}

sample_sd <- function(x) {
  n <- length(x)
  sd_val <- 0
  mean_x <- sample_mean(x)
  
  for (i in 1:n) {
    sd_val <- sd_val + (x[i] - mean_x)^2
  }
  
  sd_val <- 1/(n-1) * sd_val
  sqrt(sd_val)
}

sample_mean(c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5))
## [1] 3
sample_sd(c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5))
## [1] 1.581139

part c)

calculate_CI <- function(x, conf = 0.95) {
  alpha <- 1 - conf
  degrees_freedom <- length(x) - 1
  t_score <- qt(p = alpha / 2, df = degrees_freedom, lower.tail = FALSE)
  
  mean_x <- mean(x)
  se_x <- sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))
  lower_bound <- mean(x) - t_score*se_x
  upper_bound <- mean(x) + t_score*se_x
  
  c(lower_bound, upper_bound)
}

# Test
x <- c(1:100)
dat <- data.frame(x = x)
fit <- lm(x ~ 1, dat)

# Calculate a 95% confidence interval
confint(fit, level = 0.95)
##                2.5 %   97.5 %
## (Intercept) 44.74349 56.25651
calculate_CI(x)
## [1] 44.74349 56.25651

part b)

rainfall_plot <- function(city_name, year) {
  if (city_name %in% df$city_name == FALSE | year %in% df$year == FALSE) {
    stop()
  }
  
  df %>%
    filter(city_name == city_name, year == year) %>%
    ggplot(aes(log(rainfall))) +
    geom_histogram()
}
